# Build-time configuration for a PRODUCTION release build (OPTIONAL).
#
# These feed BuildConfig (src-tauri/src/shared/config.rs) and the release
# download page (src-tauri/src/update/commands.rs) via option_env! at COMPILE
# time. They are consumed only by the `tauri:build:release` npm script
# (`dotenv -e .env -- tauri build`). A bare `npm run tauri build` / `cargo
# build` ignores this file and falls back to safe-by-default sentinels
# (example.invalid), so the app builds and runs with auto-update effectively
# disabled and NO required release host.
#
# Auto-update is OPTIONAL and configured AFTER forking. Leave this file as-is
# (or omit .env entirely) and the app ships with the updater off. To enable
# auto-update for your fork, copy this file and set the values below to your own
# release host:
#
#   cp .env.example .env   (then run `npm run tauri:build:release` from app/)
#
# .env is gitignored; .env.example (this file) is the committed template.

# Updater manifest endpoint. Point this at your fork's release feed (e.g. a
# GitHub Releases `latest.json`). Unset -> unresolvable example.invalid sentinel
# (the update check reports "no update" without a network call).
# UPDATER_MANIFEST_URL=https://example.com/your-org/your-repo/releases/latest/download/latest.json

# Public release/download page that the "Download update" action opens. Point
# this at your fork's download page. Unset -> example.invalid sentinel.
# RELEASE_DOWNLOAD_PAGE_URL=https://example.com/your-org/your-repo/releases

# Updater public key (minisign / TUF), if your updater path uses one. Empty ->
# updates disabled.
# UPDATER_PUBKEY=

# Client app version. Omit to default to the Cargo.toml package version.
# APP_VERSION=
